            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 1</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgALICE\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgALICE', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Particles produced during the collision of protons. © CERN. (<htcite0>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Physics: Evolution of Knowledge: The Atom - In this text, we study how our idea of the atom has evolved over time. (<htcite1>)</li><li>Physics: Evolution of knowledge – The hydrogen atom - Hydrogen is the smallest atom we know of; even so, inside it we can still find other particles. (<htcite2>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
